---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ProjectStats from "../components/ProjectStats.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Project"
  description="Understand the TaMTAS mission, scientific challenge, objectives and commitment to open multilingual science."
>
  <header class="inner-hero page-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">The project</p>
    <h1>A multilingual future for scientific knowledge.</h1>
    <p>
      TaMTAS addresses two connected barriers to scientific access: language and
      complexity. It will translate scientific documents accurately, preserve their
      terminology and adapt the result for different readers.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="page-shell" data-reveal><ProjectStats /></div>

  <section class="section page-shell split-editorial">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Long-term vision</p>
      <h2>Knowledge should not depend on publishing or reading in one dominant language.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Much of scientific communication takes place in English. This creates extra
        work for researchers using other languages and limits public access to current
        knowledge.
      </p>
      <p>
        TaMTAS combines machine translation, terminology management, quality estimation,
        automatic correction and text adaptation. The intended result is a reusable
        framework for accurate and accessible scientific communication.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section objective-band">
    <div class="page-shell">
      <div class="section-heading section-heading-light">
        <p class="eyebrow">Specific objectives</p>
        <h2>Eight objectives connect research quality with public value.</h2>
      </div>
      <ol class="objective-grid">
        <li><span>01</span><p>Compile and enrich multilingual scientific corpora.</p></li>
        <li><span>02</span><p>Advance terminology extraction and integration tools.</p></li>
        <li><span>03</span><p>Train multilingual document-level translation models.</p></li>
        <li><span>04</span><p>Detect terminology errors through quality estimation.</p></li>
        <li><span>05</span><p>Correct translations with automatic post-editing.</p></li>
        <li><span>06</span><p>Adapt translated text to different audiences.</p></li>
        <li><span>07</span><p>Validate the system with real users and documents.</p></li>
        <li><span>08</span><p>Publish results through open repositories and platforms.</p></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
